         <abstract>
            <p>As an exercise for the language learner, a computerized adventure game has much to offer. Commercial examples in English exhibit impressive language-handling abilities as well as intriguing plots. Our list of the features such a program would have, if modified for instructional purposes, is followed by a description of our work to date on such a project.</p>
         </abstract>
